.SH NAME
ai \- AI prompt wrapper

.SH DESCRIPTION
Send prompts to AI using local tools first, then cloud CLI tools.
No API keys required \- uses CLI tools that handle their own authentication.

.B Local providers (use local models):
ollama, llama-cli, llama, llamafile, localai, lmstudio, gpt4all, llm, mlx, koboldcpp, jan, mods, fabric, aichat, tgpt

.B Cloud providers (use cloud APIs):
claude, copilot, gh-copilot, amazonq, cody, gemini, bito, aider, sgpt, openai, chatgpt, codex, plandex, mentat, goose, openhands, opencode, gpte

.B Providers with filesystem access (for create/build/edit commands):
claude, copilot, gemini, aichat, aider, codex, plandex, mentat, goose, openhands, opencode, gpte

.SH SYNOPSIS
ai [options] "prompt"
.br
echo "prompt" | ai

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
